    "description": "Benchmark equalizer, not default Claude Code behavior: every v2 reasoning exact/numeric task carries an answerInstruction demanding only the final answer (plain integer, decimal, or simplified fraction, one line, no working, no LaTeX), serialized by the harness as a second user text content block prefixed 'Benchmark answer format instruction:'. Budgets are moderately raised (reasoning short 700, reasoning rubric 1200, coding 1200, analysis 1500, agent_protocol 900) so visible-reasoning styles are not structurally truncated.",
    "appliedTo": "all reasoning exact/numeric tasks (answerInstructionApplied=true rows)"
  },
  "normalizationContract": "v2/format-tolerant exact+numeric grading canonicalizes answers before comparison: LaTeX wrapper stripping ($...$, \\(...\\), \\[...\\], nested \\boxed), \\frac/\\dfrac to a/b, exact reduced rational equivalence, tolerant numeric accepting integer/decimal/scientific/fraction with task tolerance or 1e-9, final-answer candidate selection (last boxed > last 'answer:' marker > per-'=' immediate candidates > last-line tokens) with conflicting-candidate rejection unless reference.values declares a list. Implemented in evals/fusion/src/grade.ts behind usesFormatTolerantScoring; v1 grading is byte-identical strict.",
  "searchEligibleDefinition": "A task is search-eligible when a well-grounded answer materially benefits from current external knowledge (present-day provider APIs, protocols, or ecosystem conventions). Tagged 'search-eligible' with searchEligible=true; the harness never forces search — profiles with search enabled may use it; rubric references describe answer structure rather than volatile facts so grounded answers score well either way.",
